&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world&#39;s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At its core, Stripe is building the financial infrastructure for the internet, and the Procurement Enablement team plays a critical role in powering that mission from within. We partner closely with internal systems teams, finance, and operational teams across Stripe&#39;s global Procurement organization to diagnose inefficiency, redesign how work gets done, and build the systems and tools that make better processes stick. As part of Procurement Enablement, you&#39;ll work at the intersection of process design, operational analytics, and emerging technology, identifying where friction exists, mapping what great looks like, and deploying AI-powered solutions as one of many tools to drive lasting operational change at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Procurement Operations and Transformation PgM, you&#39;ll combine deep process thinking, analytical rigor, and hands-on technical capability to fundamentally improve how Stripe&#39;s global procurement organization operates. You&#39;ll diagnose workflow inefficiencies, design better operating models, and build or deploy AI-powered tools that make those improvements permanent and scalable. Embedded directly within Procurement teams — Strategic Sourcing, Third Party Risk, Contracting, Procurement Operations, etc. — you&#39;ll be equally comfortable whiteboarding a process map, pulling and interpreting operational data, and shipping an automation that removes manual work for good. Your measure of success is the number of workflows you&#39;ve permanently transformed and the extent to which those in your global team start any task with an AI tool.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Identify and document the highest-leverage workflow transformations within your group&#39;s day-to-day work by understanding their processes and outputs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build and maintain a structured backlog of workflow improvement opportunities, using data and stakeholder input to sequence work effectively&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Build and deploy AI-powered tools, automations, and intelligent workflows that eliminate manual effort and enhance procurement capabilities, including autonomous agents, data products, and integrations with Stripe&#39;s procurement tech stack&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Work across Procurement Enablement and partner teams to uncover AI use cases, document requirements, and translate complex procurement workflows into scalable technical solutions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Coach and partner across Procurement through a progressive journey: from awareness, to first win, to regular AI integration, to full workflow transformation, to self-sufficiency&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Develop operating models, SOPs, and process documentation that make improved ways of working repeatable and scalable&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Teach Procurement SMEs not just to use AI tools, but to design, build, and oversee their own automated workflows over time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• 5+ years of professional experience in a role requiring critical thinking, problem-solving, and cross-functional collaboration including direct experience in procurement, supply chain, finance operations, consulting, or a related operational function&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Demonstrated, hands-on experience building AI-powered tools, agents, automations, or workflows that transformed real work processes (not just using AI as a chatbot — building with it)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Proficiency with AI development tools and platforms (e.g., Claude, Claude Code, Codex, custom agent frameworks, API integrations, and workflow automation tools)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Track record of coaching, teaching, or enabling others — formally or informally — with evidence that people you&#39;ve helped changed how they work&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Familiarity with process improvement methodologies (Lean, Six Sigma, process mapping, etc.) or structured consulting frameworks&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience with change management, organizational transformation, or large-scale enablement programs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Familiarity with Procurement technology stacks (e.g., Zip, Ramp, Oracle, etc.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Experience building and scaling internal tools, templates, or playbooks that were adopted beyond your immediate team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Background in consulting, solutions engineering, technical account management, or other client-facing technical roles&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Familiarity with the payments industry and fintech landscape&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world&#39;s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone&#39;s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Infrastructure and Data Experiences Product Team (&quot;IDX&quot; for short) is responsible for ensuring that the major Stripe engineering systems are meeting the needs of our customers—both internal teams and external users. We partner closely with Stripe&#39;s CTO, Engineering leads, and Product leads across Stripe to define technology vision, product capabilities, and roadmaps, while delivering reliable experiences for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager on the team, you&#39;ll work with Stripe tech leaders to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Grow the business through delightful user experiences and reliable infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Streamline decision making and business operations through state-of-the-art systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver the best experience for developers in the industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Stripe infrastructure is composed of high-availability distributed systems that power Stripe products. We&#39;re looking for a product manager who loves developers and works with them daily to understand their needs, has a knack for building beautiful product experiences with ergonomic user journeys, isn&#39;t afraid of understanding large technical systems, and prioritizes users and business impact. The problems you will be working on are critical to unlock the next phase of growth at Stripe, ranging from unlocking international markets through local infrastructure to powering enterprise-grade experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the engineering teams, including Core Infra, Developer Infra, Data Platform, and Service Platform, to ship functionality that delights users, has the right balance of impact vs engineering cost, and makes a measurable impact on the business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish system and design principles for how we build, buy, and operate Seller Systems—ensuring we select the right long-term solutions, not short-term patches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guide architecture and investment decisions, weighing trade-offs between build vs. buy, modernization vs. extension, and platform vs. point solution to maintain a cohesive, sustainable ecosystem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interact with external users and propose critical infrastructure abstractions that best serve them&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate product ideas and prototypes with early adopters&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define key success metrics for developer products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on infrastructure, API, and data models and pipelines roadmaps&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on internal AI agents for specific functions such as Recruiting, Legal, etc. to aid productivity and great customer experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Who you are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal Product Manager will be relentlessly user-focused, highly analytical, comfortable in ambiguity, have strong technical skills, and the desire to create something new.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of progressive experience in Product Management, ideally within an enterprise or B2B setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in defining, launching, and scaling complex products from ideation to general availability in an enterprise environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage diverse stakeholders (Engineering, Design, Sales, Marketing, Executive Leadership) and drive cross-functional alignment on product vision and prioritization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional ability to map, analyze, and refine Customer User Journeys (CUJs) to identify high-value pain points and opportunities for AI solution deployment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly data-driven approach to prioritization and decision-making, including the ability to define KPIs, create product impact dashboards, and synthesize data into actionable product requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of leveraging qualitative (customer interviews) and quantitative (product usage data) insights to validate assumptions and drive product strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to articulate complex technical concepts and product strategies clearly to both technical and non-technical audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;AI and Technical Expertise&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience developing and launching AI and ML-powered products or features for internal or external customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Robust functional and technical understanding of LLMs and common AI-based workflows (e.g., retrieval-augmented generation, fine-tuning, prompt engineering)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience working directly with LLMs or launching conversational AI agents into production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical background (e.g., Computer Science degree or equivalent practical experience) that allows for deep engagement with engineering teams on technical trade-offs and architectural decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with cross-geo and cross-timezone environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of solving high-impact, cross-system challenges and aligning senior stakeholders across Product, Engineering, and Core infrastructure organizations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;From Fivetran’s founding until now, our mission has remained the same: to make access to data as simple and reliable as electricity. With Fivetran, customer data arrives in their warehouses, canonical and ready to query, with no engineering or maintenance required. We’re proud that more organizations continue to leverage our technology every day to become truly data-driven.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Fivetran is building data pipelines to power the modern data stack for thousands of companies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for an experienced Technical Product Manager to join the Systems Engineering team and own our Quote-to-Order (QTO) systems and processes. In this role, you’ll help shape how Fivetran launches products, manages pricing, generates quotes, and executes commercial agreements at scale.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;You’ll partner closely with Sales, Product, Finance, RevOps, and Engineering to drive scalable solutions across product configuration, pricing, quoting workflows, approvals, and contract generation. A key focus of the role is enabling rapid go-to-market execution by improving how quickly new products, pricing models, and commercial structures can be introduced into our systems with high quality and operational consistency.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This role is ideal for someone who thrives in fast-moving environments, enjoys solving complex operational and systems challenges, and knows how to balance business needs, technical tradeoffs, and long-term scalability. You’re energized by bringing structure to ambiguity, asking thoughtful questions, partnering across teams, and improving the systems and processes that support how Fivetran sells and scales.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;You’ll have the opportunity to directly influence Fivetran’s go-to-market agility, operational efficiency, and revenue growth while working closely with Product, GTM, Finance, and Engineering leaders across the company.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;This is a full-time position based out of our&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;Oakland office. Our hybrid work model offers a blend of remote flexibility and in-person collaboration, including two days in the office each week to connect and build as a team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technologies You’ll Use&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Salesforce, Salesforce CPQ, IronClad, NetSuite, SQL, Looker, Lucidchart, Jira, Google Workspace, and other GTM, finance, and operational systems supporting Fivetran’s Quote-to-Order workflows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Roadmap &amp;amp; Prioritization&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Partner with GTM, Finance, Product, RevOps, and Engineering stakeholders to build and maintain the QTO systems roadmap.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Identify opportunities to improve operational efficiency, reduce friction, standardize workflows, and accelerate go-to-market execution.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Intake, triage, and assess inbound requests across pricing, quoting, contracting, and commercial operations workflows.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Evaluate business impact, operational complexity, technical feasibility, and scalability tradeoffs to help prioritize the highest-value initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements &amp;amp; Process Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Own requirements gathering and process design for prioritized QTO initiatives from discovery through delivery.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Translate ambiguous business needs into clear, actionable product and systems requirements.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ask thoughtful, detailed questions to uncover edge cases, process gaps, operational risks, and scalability concerns.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Partner with business stakeholders to simplify and standardize workflows while balancing operational needs, user experience, governance, and system constraints.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Document business processes, system behaviors, data flows, decision logic, and acceptance criteria needed to support implementation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Delivery &amp;amp; Solution Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Partner closely with Systems Engineering and technical teams to design scalable solutions across Salesforce CPQ, quoting, approvals, order management, contract workflows, and adjacent operational systems.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Help drive solution tradeoff discussions by balancing business impact, technical complexity, delivery timelines, and long-term maintainability.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Support delivery execution through backlog refinement, sprint collaboration, testing coordination, UAT support, rollout planning, and cross-functional enablement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Ensure implemented solutions align to intended business processes and operational goals.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product, Pricing &amp;amp; Commercial Systems&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Own and evolve systems and workflows supporting product catalog management, pricing structures, packaging, quoting, discounting, approvals, and commercial governance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Partner with Product, Finance, and GTM teams to operationalize new products, pricing models, and commercial motions quickly and accurately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Drive scalable approaches to consumption-based pricing, quote standardization, approval governance, and commercial process automation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Support operational readiness for product and pricing launches across systems, workflows, and enablement processes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Management &amp;amp; Operational Excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Build strong cross-functional partnerships across GTM, Finance, Product, RevOps, Legal, and Engineering teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Provide clear communication, status updates, decision framing, and prioritization transparency across initiatives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Define and track KPIs related to quoting efficiency, operational accuracy, launch readiness, adoption, and process health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0) !important; font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;Measure and communicate the operational and business impact of delivered initiatives and identify opportunities for continuous improvement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
